                  </persName>
            . I took the prisoner at Mr. Fox's house; he said if he would forgive him he would never do so again.</p>
               <p>HENRY HARRIS FOX. I saw the prisoner, and heard him say something, but did not distinctly hear what it was.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. There was my master and another man in the house, and when the man was gone the spoon was missed - I never saw it.</p>
